<DIV style="position:absolute;top:281;left:279"><nobr><span class="ft10">The housing market is a bubble<br>waiting to happen. There is a<br>moderate risk that the bubble<br>will burst in the next five years<br>and cause a minor recession.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:281;left:463"><nobr><span class="ft16"><b>High.</b> If the bubble bursts, it<br>will be significant. This is a risk<br>factor only.</span></nobr></DIV>
<DIV style="position:absolute;top:305;left:672"><nobr><span class="ft14">↓</span></nobr></DIV>
